SUMMARY:Drawing the Costumed Model
DESCRIPTION:Overview\n*New*  An informal costumed life drawing session\, the last Tuesday each month at Gwartzman’s! Join fellow creatives\, practice techniques\, experiment and relax. \nWhat to expect \nDoors will open at 6:30pm. Each month will feature different costumes and models. We will start with short pose/quick gesture\, and progressively move into longer poses at approximately 15-20 minutes in length. There will be a short break half way through. \nWhat to bring \nDry drawing media is encouraged. Here are some suggestions from our team: \nNewsprint Pad/ Pencil Set/ Charcoal/ Conte \nIf you need to pick up any materials in store\, our staff will be happy to assist!* Limited boards/clips\, and table easels will be available to borrow. \nHow to get here \nWe are at College and Spadina. The 506 and 510 streetcar are the closest options.
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/drawing-the-costumed-model/
LOCATION:448 Spadina Avenue\, 448 Spadina Ave.\, Toronto\, ON M5T 2G8\, Canada\, Old Toronto\, Toronto\, Ontario\, M5T 2G8
CATEGORIES:Art & Design,Classes & Workshops
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/drawing-the-costumed-model.png
END:VEVENT
