SUMMARY:Movie Night @ Soulpepper: Earth's Greatest Enemy
DESCRIPTION:Join Soulpepper Theatre for a screening of the new documentary Earth’s Greatest Enemy on Tuesday March 31 at 7pm.  \nFrom journalist and director Abby Martin\, Earth’s Greatest Enemy is a documentary uncovering the role of the U.S. military\, its NATO allies and defense contractors in the climate crisis. Combining investigative journalism\, striking visuals\, and stories from impacted communities\, the film challenges audiences to rethink the hidden costs of a global military empire and its planetary consequences. \nIn a moment when the world has its eyes on increasingly expansive impacts of both military operations and climate change\, this revelatory documentary sheds light on the interplay between both. \nFree general admission. Book tickets in advance: https://www.soulpepper.ca/public-domain/whats-on/earthsgreatestenemy 
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/movie-night-soulpepper-earths-greatest-enemy/
LOCATION:Soulpepper Theatre Co\, 50 Tank House Lane\, Toronto\, ON M5A 3C4\, Canada\, Old Toronto\, Toronto\, Ontario\, M5A 3C4
CATEGORIES:Film & Media,Theatre & Opera
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/movie-night-soulpepper-earths-greatest-enemy.png
END:VEVENT
