SUMMARY:Rhinoceros
DESCRIPTION:Absurdity runs rampant as a quiet town succumbs to herd mentality\, transforming into beasts of conformity. A sharp and surreal allegory on resistance. \nPresented by Performance at Toronto Metropolitan University \nWritten by Eugene IonescoDirected by Cynthia Ashperger \nPlease be advised that the performance on Mar. 31st is a preview performance. \nWe offer our tickets on a sliding scale model between $5-$50. \nThe different price points allow you to choose what ticket price makes the most sense for you – the lower price points are intended for students\, arts-workers\, and people who have low/precarious income; the higher price points are intended for those with reliable income and/or other assets/savings. \nAll tickets provide the same level of entry to the event. \nAll ticket proceeds go back to support Performance at The Creative School.
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/rhinoceros/
LOCATION:School of Performance at Toronto Metropolitan University\, 345 Yonge St\, Toronto\, ON M5B\, Toronto\, ON M5B 2K3\, Canada\, Toronto\, Old Toronto\, Ontario\, M5B 2K3
CATEGORIES:Performing Arts,Theatre & Opera
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/rhinoceros.png
END:VEVENT
